<h1>RF CMOS Linearity Metrics and Formulas</h1>

<h2>IP3 (Third-Order Intercept Point)</h2>
<p>Measures how a system handles third-order intermodulation distortion (IMD3).</p>
<p>\[
IP3 = P_{out} + \frac{1}{2}(P_{out} - P_{3rd})
\]</p>
<p><strong>Units</strong>: dBm</p>

<h2>1-dB Compression Point (P1dB)</h2>
<p>Output power level at which the system deviates from linear behavior by 1 dB.</p>
<p>\[
P_{out} = P_{in} + Gain \quad (\text{linear region}) \\
P_{out} = P_{in} + Gain - 1 \quad (\text{at 1-dB compression})
\]</p>
<p><strong>Units</strong>: dBm</p>

<h2>IP2 (Second-Order Intercept Point)</h2>
<p>Indicates how a system handles second-order intermodulation distortion.</p>
<p>\[
IP2 = P_{out} + \frac{1}{2}(P_{out} - P_{2nd})
\]</p>
<p><strong>Units</strong>: dBm</p>

<h2>Spurious-Free Dynamic Range (SFDR)</h2>
<p>Measures the difference between the desired signal and the strongest undesired signal.</p>
<p>\[
SFDR = P_{signal} - P_{spurious}
\]</p>
<p><strong>Units</strong>: dB</p>

<h2>Harmonic Distortion (HD)</h2>
<p>Evaluates how much a circuit produces harmonics of the input frequencies.</p>
<p>\[
HD = \frac{P_{harmonic}}{P_{fundamental}}
\]</p>
<p><strong>Units</strong>: Ratio or dB</p>

<h2>OIP3 and IIP3</h2>
<p>Output and input-referred third-order intercept points, respectively.</p>
<p>\[
OIP3 = P_{out} + \frac{(P_{out} - P_{3rd})}{2} \\
IIP3 = OIP3 - Gain
\]</p>
<p><strong>Units</strong>: dBm</p>

<h2>HD2 and HD3</h2>
<p>Second and third harmonic distortions, respectively.</p>
<p>\[
HD2 = \frac{P_{2nd harmonic}}{P_{fundamental}} \\
HD3 = \frac{P_{3rd harmonic}}{P_{fundamental}}
\]</p>
<p><strong>Units</strong>: Ratio or dB</p>

<h2>IM2 and IM3</h2>
<p>Second and third intermodulation products.</p>
<p>\[
IM2 = 2f_1 \pm f_2 \\
IM3 = 2f_1 \pm f_2, 2f_2 \pm f_1
\]</p>
<p><strong>Units</strong>: Frequency (Hz)</p>

<h2>TOI (Third Order Input)</h2>
<p>Another measure of linearity that quantifies how the amplitude of third-order intermodulation products grows.</p>
<p>\[
TOI = P_{in} + \frac{(P_{out} - P_{3rd})}{2}
\]</p>
<p><strong>Units</strong>: dBm</p>

<h2>IMD (Intermodulation Distortion)</h2>
<p>Measures the unwanted signals generated when two or more signals are present.</p>
<p>\[
IMD = 20 \times \log\left(\frac{P_{out}}{P_{IMD}}\right)
\]</p>
<p><strong>Units</strong>: dB</p>

